STAT 547: Homework 09

Welcome to the repository!

This material is all about automated analyis and pipelines, using the make functionality in R.

Most of the material here is an extension of Shaun Jackman and Jenny Bryans activity from STAT 545.

My additions include:

  • Added an .R script hist_vowels.R, which uses the stringr package to create a frequency table of vowels in the English language.

  • Added an .rmd script report2.rmd that creates an .html and .md report from the outputs of the vowels analysis.

  • Added both of the new scripts to the project makefile, and added a the creation of a graph for the vowels analysis. I then updated the relevant dependencies.
